WEBVTT

00:01.083 --> 00:02.750
[Meredith] <i>Previously on </i>Grey's Anatomy...

00:02.834 --> 00:04.166
OK, Cindy Wright.

00:04.250 --> 00:05.166
<i>She fits the profile.</i>

00:05.250 --> 00:06.667
Arrest this woman for child trafficking!

00:06.750 --> 00:08.583
[Bailey] Please escort
Dr. DeLuca to my office.

00:08.667 --> 00:10.250
What? Me?!
What, you're just gonna let her go?

00:10.542 --> 00:12.000
I did the job that needed to be done!

00:12.083 --> 00:13.041
Andrew, you sound like your father.

00:13.125 --> 00:14.166
This is Gemma.

00:14.250 --> 00:15.917
-Uh, she's a friend.
-I can see that.

00:16.208 --> 00:17.917
Something's wrong with me.
What's happening?

00:18.208 --> 00:20.291
[DeLuca] <i>Cobalt poisoning would explain</i>
<i>the dementia, the depression,</i>

00:20.375 --> 00:22.291
hallucinations, tremors-- everything.

00:22.375 --> 00:23.959
Is your mind playing tricks on you again?

00:24.041 --> 00:26.041
[Richard] <i>Did you stand by me</i>
<i>while I was being fired?</i>

00:26.125 --> 00:27.667
I'm tired of telling you that I want more.

00:27.750 --> 00:29.041
I hope you find someone
who will give that to you.

00:29.291 --> 00:30.250
Dr. Winston Ndugu.

00:30.333 --> 00:32.792
I have had a crush on you
since my first day of residency.

00:32.875 --> 00:34.375
[Link]
<i>What do you think of the name Scout?</i>

00:34.583 --> 00:35.500
So cute. [chuckles]

00:35.583 --> 00:37.000
-We're getting married.
-I want a life with you.

00:37.083 --> 00:38.834
[Koracick] <i>Are you really sure</i>
<i>you want to close this door?</i>

00:38.917 --> 00:39.875
A voicemail from Dr. Altman.

00:39.959 --> 00:42.125
[Teddy groaning] <i>I can't leave with you.</i>

00:42.208 --> 00:43.166
<i>I am marrying Owen.</i>

00:43.250 --> 00:45.417
I'm so sorry, honey. We'll reschedule.

00:45.542 --> 00:46.917
Why are we rescheduling?

00:51.417 --> 00:53.625
[Meredith] <i>I've heard</i>
<i>that when tidal waves hit,</i>

00:53.709 --> 00:55.875
<i>there are often people watching on shore.</i>

01:00.333 --> 01:04.166
<i>They see the disaster coming,</i>
<i>see the horizon disappearing.</i>

01:04.250 --> 01:07.291
<i>They don't really see until it's too late.</i>

01:09.667 --> 01:11.250
<i>There's a lecture we take in residency</i>

01:11.333 --> 01:14.041
<i>that's meant to prepare us</i>
<i>for such surprises.</i>

01:14.125 --> 01:16.333
<i>It's called Disaster Ethics--</i>

01:16.417 --> 01:19.166
<i>where future surgeons imagine</i>
<i>what they would do</i>

01:19.250 --> 01:21.125
<i>when the unimaginable happens.</i>

01:24.875 --> 01:28.041
[gasps]

01:28.125 --> 01:29.625
<i>But it's imperfect.</i>

01:30.875 --> 01:34.125
<i>Because while it's good</i>
<i>to plan for the worst,</i>

01:34.208 --> 01:36.834
<i>you can't really know how you'll handle it</i>

01:36.917 --> 01:39.500
<i>until you're smack dab</i>
<i>in the middle of it,</i>

01:39.583 --> 01:42.625
<i>under the wave, trying not to drown.</i>

01:48.709 --> 01:51.583
-[cheers and applause]
-[Ben] Thank you!

01:51.667 --> 01:54.375
Yes! Thank you, all!

01:55.000 --> 01:55.875
OK.

02:11.625 --> 02:13.583
I'll see you after the shift change.

02:13.959 --> 02:14.917
You be careful out there.

02:15.000 --> 02:16.667
You be careful <i>in </i>there.

02:17.458 --> 02:19.542
We are doing everything right.

02:19.625 --> 02:22.458
We are wearing masks.
We are wearing gloves.

02:22.542 --> 02:23.959
We are slowing the spread.

02:24.041 --> 02:27.000
I am good and my family is g--

02:28.125 --> 02:31.417
Oh, please don't tell me
you're experiencing symptoms.

02:31.500 --> 02:34.875
I am absolutely not
experiencing any symptoms.

02:34.959 --> 02:36.500
I'm here to work.

02:37.625 --> 02:38.834
I'm cobalt free, Miranda.

02:38.917 --> 02:41.083
I've done my hip rehab.
I'm better than ever.

02:41.166 --> 02:43.458
Just tell me where you want me,
but don't say back home.

02:43.542 --> 02:44.792
Well, everything's changed.

02:44.875 --> 02:47.542
I mean, specialties no longer matter.

02:47.625 --> 02:49.542
Surgeons check temperatures.

02:49.667 --> 02:52.208
Attendings do scut. It's a madhouse.

02:52.291 --> 02:53.166
On fire.

02:53.250 --> 02:54.583
Well, you better show me around.

02:54.667 --> 02:55.542
Unless you're too busy.

02:55.625 --> 02:57.625
You can send me off with a resident.

02:57.709 --> 02:59.542
You know, I'd love to say hello to DeLuca.

03:00.709 --> 03:03.500
[tape rewinds]

03:03.583 --> 03:05.834
DeLuca is no longer a resident.

03:05.917 --> 03:07.750
So, Andrew's in the on-call room on 3.

03:07.834 --> 03:08.959
He didn't even want to come in today,

03:09.041 --> 03:11.166
but I didn't think
he should be alone, so...

03:11.250 --> 03:14.792
Right. Because you're so concerned
about his well-being.

03:14.875 --> 03:16.166
This is unbelievable.

03:16.250 --> 03:17.458
What happened with DeLuca now?

03:17.542 --> 03:19.667
He could barely get up
after Richard's surgery.

03:19.750 --> 03:22.166
It's the depression that
always comes after the mania.

03:22.250 --> 03:24.542
You knew this happens,
b-but you pushed him anyways.

03:24.625 --> 03:25.500
And you let her.

03:29.250 --> 03:32.583
First stop for every employee.
A few questions.

03:32.709 --> 03:36.125
And if your temperature's
even a hair over 100 degrees,

03:36.208 --> 03:38.125
you go back home. No exceptions.

03:38.208 --> 03:41.000
And once you're cleared--
here, get in here--

03:41.083 --> 03:42.291
you will change

03:42.375 --> 03:44.375
and be fitted with a new N95.

03:45.375 --> 03:47.417
All right, let's move it.

03:47.500 --> 03:49.500
[cellphone rings]

03:49.583 --> 03:51.000
[Winston, over FaceTime]
<i>How was the picnic?</i>

03:51.083 --> 03:52.834
[Maggie]
It turned into a sleepover, actually.

03:52.917 --> 03:55.333
[<i>chuckles</i>] <i>On the laundry-room floor?</i>

03:55.375 --> 03:56.667
Yeah, Zola didn't want me to leave,

03:56.750 --> 03:59.125
and I-I was too tired
to go back to the hotel room.

03:59.208 --> 04:01.542
So she had a picnic on the kitchen floor,

04:01.625 --> 04:03.542
<i>and I got takeout.</i>

04:03.625 --> 04:06.500
<i>And we talked to each other</i>
<i>through the closed door,</i>

04:06.583 --> 04:08.709
and then I made a bed

04:08.792 --> 04:10.375
out of some baby blankets
I found in the dryer.

04:10.458 --> 04:12.500
-You are such a good aunt.
-[chuckles]

04:12.583 --> 04:14.583
Yeah, my back is killing me,

04:14.709 --> 04:17.333
<i>but it sure beats lying</i>
<i>in my hotel-room bed</i>

04:17.417 --> 04:19.917
and watching terrifying
statistics on the news

04:20.000 --> 04:21.625
and knowing that's not even
half the story.

04:21.709 --> 04:23.709
Yeah. I tried explaining to my grandma

04:23.792 --> 04:25.750
how this is impacting
Black folks more severely.

04:25.834 --> 04:28.041
<i>But all she wants to talk</i>
<i>about is how sacrilegious it is</i>

04:28.125 --> 04:29.583
<i>to attend church </i><i>on a computer.</i>

04:29.667 --> 04:31.041
[laughs]

04:31.125 --> 04:33.125
[Kingsley]
Dr. Ndugu, we have a dissection.

04:33.208 --> 04:34.583
Uh, I gotta go, babe. Love you.

04:34.667 --> 04:37.458
[cellphone beeps]

04:37.542 --> 04:38.583
-Love you?
-Hm?

04:40.166 --> 04:41.500
Were you eavesdropping on my call?

04:41.583 --> 04:43.000
Not on purpose.

04:44.333 --> 04:45.917
Sounds like things
are going pretty well, though,

04:46.000 --> 04:47.583
if you're at "love you" already.

04:47.667 --> 04:48.917
Well, we're not. I'm not-- We're--

04:49.000 --> 04:52.250
That's just-- That's just,
like, a-a thing people say.

04:52.333 --> 04:54.250
By rote. Is it?

04:54.375 --> 04:56.041
How's Vic?

04:56.166 --> 04:58.750
It's really nice of them
to clap us in and out every day.

04:58.834 --> 05:01.125
I-- [sighs] I really appreciate that.

05:01.208 --> 05:03.625
-Yeah.
-Yeah. It really is.

05:03.709 --> 05:04.667
It's nice.

05:04.750 --> 05:06.959
[tape rewinds]

05:07.041 --> 05:09.458
[Jackson mimicking airplane engine]

05:09.542 --> 05:11.125
-[doorbell rings]
-Ooh, we have a visitor.

05:11.208 --> 05:14.792
Who is here coming to visit us?

05:14.875 --> 05:15.750
[sighs]

05:17.375 --> 05:19.208
[Vic] Hey, hey, hey, I'm--

05:19.291 --> 05:20.667
-Oh, hey!
-Oh!

05:20.750 --> 05:22.500
-Uh, what is--
-Oh! No.

05:22.583 --> 05:24.166
What is going on? Hi.

05:24.250 --> 05:25.458
No, no. Um...

05:26.208 --> 05:27.208
I thought--

05:27.291 --> 05:29.959
We were texting and you said
to come over with nothing on.

05:30.041 --> 05:31.959
-I didn't mean right now.
-So you-- OK.

05:32.333 --> 05:34.750
-OK. Um, sorry. I'm sorry. Hello?
-Hi.

05:34.834 --> 05:37.375
-Come on--
-No, no, you know what? Actually. No.

05:37.458 --> 05:39.166
It's fine. It's OK. It's good.

05:39.250 --> 05:40.959
It's not that... cold out, actually,

05:41.041 --> 05:42.959
-so I'm just-- I'm gonna go.
-Hey. No, you don't need to leave.

05:43.041 --> 05:44.500
No, I do. I have to, OK?

05:44.583 --> 05:45.917
This is...

05:47.083 --> 05:48.125
This was good.

05:48.208 --> 05:51.291
<i>This </i>was a mistake. But this whole thing.

05:51.375 --> 05:52.667
I'm not a...

05:54.000 --> 05:55.834
I'm not a stepmom.

05:57.041 --> 05:58.834
You're not a stepmom.

05:58.917 --> 06:02.750
I'm just-- I'm a person
who shows up at penthouses

06:02.834 --> 06:05.208
wearing puffy coats
and nothing else, so...

06:05.291 --> 06:06.250
Yeah.

06:07.458 --> 06:08.792
Wow. OK.

06:08.875 --> 06:12.083
Um, this was too much too soon.

06:12.166 --> 06:13.291
Thank you.

06:14.083 --> 06:16.333
Hi, Harriett, it was really nice--

06:16.417 --> 06:18.959
really nice to meet you
after all this time.

06:19.041 --> 06:21.542
Um, OK, bye.

06:21.625 --> 06:23.208
Godspeed.

06:23.291 --> 06:25.041
-[Perez] Next.
-[man] This happens when I eat nuts,

06:25.125 --> 06:26.500
but I didn't eat any nuts.

06:26.583 --> 06:29.250
-Uh, I don't think.
-Those food labels are small.

06:29.333 --> 06:30.417
-Here.
-[thermometer beeps]

06:30.500 --> 06:31.917
OK, 98.6.

06:32.000 --> 06:33.500
So you are going to want to follow

06:33.583 --> 06:34.834
the purple line to the ER.

06:34.917 --> 06:36.583
I don't want a Chinese doctor.

06:37.834 --> 06:39.458
Oh, OK.

06:39.542 --> 06:40.500
Then you're going to want to follow

06:40.583 --> 06:42.041
this green line to the parking lot,

06:42.125 --> 06:43.667
put your rude self back in your car

06:43.750 --> 06:46.291
and hope you don't go into
anaphylactic shock.

06:47.917 --> 06:49.709
I'll follow the purple line to the ER.

06:49.792 --> 06:51.250
Perfect.

06:52.458 --> 06:54.500
OMG. Dr. Webber.

06:54.583 --> 06:56.250
You look great. Hearts.

06:56.333 --> 06:57.333
Perez.

06:57.417 --> 06:58.625
Next.

06:58.750 --> 07:01.000
[indistinct conversations]

07:01.125 --> 07:02.375
Hey.

07:02.458 --> 07:04.792
Can you please make sure
this gets up to the Covid floor

07:04.875 --> 07:07.041
-with Enna Ravera?
-Just leave it.

07:07.125 --> 07:09.166
Uh, hey, Karen, uh, could I get an update

07:09.542 --> 07:11.166
for Ike Donerson?
He's a friend of a friend.

07:11.250 --> 07:13.083
Happy to check on him for you, Dr. Hunt.

07:13.667 --> 07:15.500
-Hope the kids are doing OK.
-Oh, thanks.

07:15.583 --> 07:18.542
Um, my mom's hands are full,
but she's managing.

07:19.959 --> 07:21.542
[Bailey] There's another tent for visitors

07:21.625 --> 07:23.375
'cause none are allowed in the hospital

07:23.458 --> 07:25.083
unless accompanying a young child.

07:25.166 --> 07:27.709
-[Owen] Dr. Webber?
-Ah, Hunt.

07:27.792 --> 07:30.583
Altman. I-I-Is it still Altman?

07:30.667 --> 07:33.792
-Yeah, still Altman.
-Ah.

07:33.875 --> 07:36.083
I hate to leave,
but I-I-I got to get back.

07:36.166 --> 07:37.959
Yeah, and I-I've got another--

07:38.041 --> 07:40.625
-Uh.
-All right, the less severe symptoms

07:40.709 --> 07:42.125
are sent home to self-quarantine.

07:42.208 --> 07:43.792
The more severe are admitted.

07:44.125 --> 07:46.875
The entire OR heard a recording

07:46.959 --> 07:50.375
of Altman and Koracick having sex...

07:50.458 --> 07:53.250
-[sighs]
-...or was that the cobalt talking?

07:54.500 --> 07:56.959
-That was not the cobalt.
-Ooh!

07:57.041 --> 07:58.583
[chuckling] Stop it. Stop it.

07:58.667 --> 07:59.709
-You're bad. Stop it.
-Stop?

07:59.792 --> 08:01.792
I came back just so
I could ask the question.

08:01.875 --> 08:03.083
[both laugh]

08:03.166 --> 08:04.250
-[Bailey] What is wrong--
-What?

08:07.208 --> 08:09.750
[Bailey] The entire east wing
is now a Covid ward.

08:09.834 --> 08:13.000
We've converted whole floors
into negative pressure rooms.

08:13.083 --> 08:16.333
Severe patients go to
this special Covid ICU.

08:16.417 --> 08:18.166
So far we have enough ventilators.

08:18.250 --> 08:20.709
Well, what about PPE for the staff?

08:20.792 --> 08:22.417
We are reusing what we have,

08:22.500 --> 08:23.709
-but we need more-- a lot--
-Wait.

08:23.792 --> 08:25.792
-No, no, no, no.
-Well, someone's coding here.

08:25.875 --> 08:29.000
Uh, and we have staff inside
to deal with it.

08:29.083 --> 08:31.166
Look, hospitals are losing
too many of their own.

08:31.250 --> 08:34.208
So no one goes through
those doors without full PPE,

08:34.291 --> 08:35.625
which is in short supply.

08:35.709 --> 08:37.750
Yes, it goes against everything we teach,

08:37.834 --> 08:40.125
but there are no emergencies
in a pandemic.

08:40.208 --> 08:42.125
Marvin Lindstrom. 83.

08:42.208 --> 08:46.166
He was fine yesterday,
became hypoxic an hour ago.

08:46.250 --> 08:48.834
It's the fourth patient I've lost today,

08:48.917 --> 08:50.458
and they're all dying alone.

08:50.542 --> 08:52.583
Welcome back, Richard.

09:03.083 --> 09:05.917
Hey, so, bed 4 needs
to go up for CT, OK?

09:06.000 --> 09:08.625
-[man] Still has pain in the chest?
-[woman] Yes.

09:08.709 --> 09:10.500
[siren wails]

09:12.125 --> 09:13.208
-Hughes, we're not taking--
-[Vic] No, I know.

09:13.291 --> 09:14.834
I know you're not taking
any non-Covid cases,

09:14.917 --> 09:17.166
but you are taking this teenager
with full thickness burns

09:17.250 --> 09:18.667
from head to toe from a car explosion.

09:18.750 --> 09:19.750
I intubated him on the scene.

09:19.834 --> 09:21.542
He's hypotensive and tachycardic
and you are the best

09:21.625 --> 09:23.625
so you are taking him because
if you send us away, he dies,

09:23.709 --> 09:25.250
and that makes you a murderer.

09:25.333 --> 09:26.417
-OK.
-OK.

09:26.500 --> 09:27.917
Trauma 1.

09:28.000 --> 09:29.834
You were right to bring him here.

09:32.208 --> 09:36.583
Emergent surgeries only,
so it's empty most of the time.

09:36.667 --> 09:39.125
-Oh, how the mighty have fallen.
-[cellphone dings, vibrates]

09:39.208 --> 09:41.834
I try not to look at it. Too sad.

09:44.250 --> 09:46.125
Bailey, what the hell is that?

09:46.250 --> 09:49.000
Oh, not that, <i>her.</i>

09:52.166 --> 09:54.083
[Bailey] She's my new best friend.

09:54.166 --> 09:55.917
She hates germs as much as I do.

09:56.000 --> 09:57.500
Uh, see that UV light?

09:57.583 --> 09:59.709
It can disinfect a room in minutes.

09:59.792 --> 10:01.125
Hands-free. [laughs]

10:01.208 --> 10:03.709
That's incredible.

10:03.792 --> 10:06.542
I used to go see babies
when I needed serotonin.

10:06.625 --> 10:09.208
But they don't let visitors
on the OB floor anymore.

10:09.291 --> 10:10.667
So now I come see her.

10:10.750 --> 10:13.917
She's sleek, beautiful, she hates germs.

10:14.000 --> 10:16.792
-I love her.
-[Koracick] Uh, do my eyes deceive me?

10:16.875 --> 10:19.125
Captain Cobalt, welcome back.

10:19.208 --> 10:20.792
-[Bailey] Ugh.
-What, too soon?

10:20.875 --> 10:22.667
No, in all seriousness,

10:22.750 --> 10:24.583
I'm so happy to see you
on your feet again.

10:24.667 --> 10:26.125
What's with the nine iron?

10:26.208 --> 10:28.291
Oh, well, this way
you won't get any closer

10:28.375 --> 10:29.417
than, uh, six feet from me.

10:29.500 --> 10:31.750
You don't need a golf club for that, Tom.

10:31.834 --> 10:32.959
Any word on the shipment?

10:33.041 --> 10:34.917
Uh, relax, Bailey.
I said it's coming, it's coming.

10:35.000 --> 10:37.333
What, you got N95s and face shields?

10:37.417 --> 10:40.458
Because there's pirates
out there and hucksters.

10:40.542 --> 10:42.083
[sighs]

10:42.166 --> 10:43.458
Has Catherine been coming in?

10:43.542 --> 10:44.959
-[cellphone dings, vibrates]
-Sometimes.

10:45.041 --> 10:47.583
-Uh, Richard, I've got a trauma.
-Oh, I'll come.

10:47.667 --> 10:50.583
No, you go read the safety manuals

10:50.667 --> 10:52.166
and memorize the new protocols.

10:52.250 --> 10:55.083
Can't let anything
fall through the cracks.

10:55.166 --> 10:56.250
Or anyone.

10:59.792 --> 11:01.000
Can I help you?

11:01.083 --> 11:04.041
A patient of your brother's
would like to see him.

11:04.125 --> 11:06.959
-No. Absolutely not.
-It's Cindy Wright.

11:07.041 --> 11:09.000
The girl he said was being trafficked.

11:09.083 --> 11:10.667
It appears he was right.

11:10.792 --> 11:13.625
S-She's here? Is she OK?

11:13.709 --> 11:17.000
She is here but I would not say
she is OK.

11:17.083 --> 11:19.417
No, Bailey, you need to stop doing this.

11:19.500 --> 11:21.291
I-I wouldn't be here
if it were anyone else.

11:21.375 --> 11:23.375
But I think he's
the only person in the world

11:23.458 --> 11:24.750
she trusts right now.

11:28.166 --> 11:30.834
-Oh, my--
-[sighs]

11:30.917 --> 11:32.458
[sighs]

11:37.083 --> 11:38.250
[sighs]

11:38.333 --> 11:39.333
You sure about this?

11:39.417 --> 11:40.792
No.

11:54.083 --> 11:55.458
-Hey.
-[Cindy] I'm so sorry.

11:56.542 --> 11:58.166
I'm sorry I didn't listen,
but I was scared.

11:58.250 --> 12:01.125
You do not need to apologize
for anything, OK?

12:02.041 --> 12:03.458
I'm just glad you came back.

12:06.041 --> 12:07.875
Walk me through what happened.
How did you get here?

12:09.583 --> 12:12.875
I got sicker, and Opal said I was useless.

12:14.041 --> 12:16.375
She dropped me off
on the side of the interstate.

12:17.458 --> 12:19.291
But I remembered the name of this place.

12:19.709 --> 12:20.583
And you.

12:21.917 --> 12:23.583
Chief, do you mind if I go in with her?

12:23.667 --> 12:25.750
-I'll throw on some lead.
-Of course.

12:35.625 --> 12:37.834
Isn't DeLuca...

12:37.917 --> 12:39.709
I mean, people have been saying he--

12:39.792 --> 12:41.083
Get the man a vest.

12:55.959 --> 12:57.000
[ringing]

12:57.083 --> 12:58.333
-[Levi] <i>Hi.</i>
-Schmitt.

12:59.750 --> 13:01.083
Marvin Lindstrom just died.

13:01.166 --> 13:04.333
[sighs] No. Please, no.

13:04.417 --> 13:06.959
I tried calling his wife.
It rolled to voicemail.

13:07.041 --> 13:09.000
<i>-Are you with her?</i>
-She's here.

13:09.375 --> 13:11.166
Her flip phone died,
and we didn't have a charger.

13:11.917 --> 13:13.375
She wanted to say goodbye to him.

13:13.458 --> 13:15.291
Well, I wanted that, too, Schmitt.

13:15.375 --> 13:17.417
There just wasn't time.
It happened so fast.

13:18.583 --> 13:21.041
They were married 62 years.

13:21.125 --> 13:22.875
<i>I held his hand </i><i>while he died.</i>

13:22.959 --> 13:25.000
So if you can't deliver the news to her,

13:25.083 --> 13:27.333
just find someone who can.

13:27.417 --> 13:30.250
-[cellphone beeps]
-[sighs]

13:31.125 --> 13:32.041
[Bailey] What do we have?

13:32.125 --> 13:33.709
[Owen] Engine blew when
he was trying to cool it down.

13:33.792 --> 13:34.875
It started a fire.

13:34.959 --> 13:36.917
He's got extensive full-thickness burns.

13:37.000 --> 13:38.041
-Let's hang some fluids.
-[woman] On it.

13:38.125 --> 13:41.000
Kids decided to break quarantine,
went out to a party.

13:41.083 --> 13:42.333
A party? Now?

13:42.417 --> 13:44.583
OK, I gotta call my kids
and threaten them.

13:44.667 --> 13:46.959
You want, uh, back up?
Want me to page Altman?

13:47.041 --> 13:47.959
No, no, no, we're good.

13:48.041 --> 13:49.500
He's hypotensive.

13:49.583 --> 13:51.417
Arms are all charred.

13:51.500 --> 13:53.291
