-[woman] Right away, Doctor.

13:56.041 --> 13:57.458
[Owen] OK, here we go.

13:59.166 --> 14:00.834
Order a trauma panel.
Let's get x-ray in here.

14:00.917 --> 14:01.959
His sats are still dropping.

14:02.041 --> 14:03.375
He's getting harder to bag.

14:03.458 --> 14:05.458
These chest burns are preventing
his lungs from expanding.

14:05.542 --> 14:07.250
-[sighs] Escharotomy. Scalpel.
-Escharotomy. Scalpel.

14:15.917 --> 14:17.417
[Jackson] Alright, we need to get
this kid to an OR

14:17.500 --> 14:19.500
-and start debriding, ASAP.
-[Owen] Yeah, I already paged for help.

14:19.583 --> 14:20.500
I need to stay down here.

14:20.583 --> 14:21.917
There's other kids coming in
from this fire.

14:22.000 --> 14:24.000
-All right, copy that.
-[Jo] Hey, Hunt, I got your page.

14:24.083 --> 14:25.333
And here's your help.

14:26.417 --> 14:27.875
[tape rewinds]

14:32.792 --> 14:33.917
Everything OK?

14:34.000 --> 14:36.000
-Yeah.
-Yeah. Great.

14:38.542 --> 14:40.583
OK. Let's get ready to move.

14:47.000 --> 14:48.000
[man] Watch your back.

14:50.750 --> 14:51.667
[sighs]

14:54.709 --> 14:58.208
You hear this, uh, kid
was out partying with friends?

14:59.458 --> 15:01.458
I don't know what the hell
these kids are thinking.

15:02.583 --> 15:06.000
Yeah, well, people do stupid things.

15:10.834 --> 15:13.083
-[knock on door]
-Hey.

15:13.166 --> 15:14.500
Hey.

15:14.583 --> 15:17.709
I'm, uh, about to be done here
if you need the room.

15:17.792 --> 15:20.709
No, actually, I was looking for you.

15:20.792 --> 15:22.583
I need a favor.

15:22.667 --> 15:23.834
Cool. Consult?

15:23.917 --> 15:25.417
Yeah, kind of.

15:25.500 --> 15:27.208
Um... [chuckles]

15:27.291 --> 15:30.125
Actually, no, not-- not like a consult.

15:30.208 --> 15:31.291
Um...

15:31.375 --> 15:32.542
S--

15:32.625 --> 15:33.500
Sex.

15:33.583 --> 15:34.458
What's that?

15:34.542 --> 15:35.375
[Jo] Sex.

15:35.458 --> 15:37.083
I need sex.

15:37.166 --> 15:39.208
I need a sex favor.

15:39.291 --> 15:40.959
A sexual favor.

15:43.291 --> 15:45.333
[clears throat] I-- W-What?

15:45.417 --> 15:50.083
I need a bridge over the river
of the husband who abandoned me.

15:50.166 --> 15:51.083
A short bridge.

15:51.166 --> 15:55.709
No, like a-- like a one-night bridge.

15:57.667 --> 15:59.583
I-I can't tell if you're
being serious. Are you--

15:59.667 --> 16:02.667
Look, I don't know how to be
single or feel single again.

16:02.750 --> 16:05.917
I just-- I-I don't know how
to cross over the bridge

16:06.000 --> 16:09.875
over into the land of Not a Sad Sack.

16:09.959 --> 16:12.750
Of Not a-- The land of Not a Sad Sack?

16:12.834 --> 16:16.083
-OK.
-OK, I-I need to have sex, Jackson.

16:16.166 --> 16:17.792
With someone that I trust to be safe

16:17.875 --> 16:20.166
and-- and just not murder me in my sleep.

16:20.250 --> 16:22.417
And I need a bridge, so I'm asking.

16:22.500 --> 16:24.959
I am truly asking for a favor.

16:25.083 --> 16:26.834
A sexy favor.

16:26.917 --> 16:28.792
OK, and you-- and you can say no

16:28.875 --> 16:33.041
if you feel used
or objectified or whatever,

16:33.125 --> 16:35.083
but I hope that you just feel flattered

16:35.166 --> 16:39.333
because I'm mostly saying
that you're a human male

16:39.417 --> 16:42.000
that I kind of trust.

16:44.333 --> 16:45.166
OK.

16:45.291 --> 16:47.792
Like, <i>OK </i>OK?

16:47.875 --> 16:49.959
I mean, it's not exactly a hardship, Jo.

16:50.041 --> 16:52.834
Oh, my God. OK. Um... tonight?

16:52.917 --> 16:54.792
-Sure. Yeah.
-OK.

16:54.875 --> 16:56.750
-My-- My place?
-OK. Yes!

16:56.834 --> 16:59.208
Thank you. Thank you. You're the best.

16:59.291 --> 17:01.375
-Thanks.
-OK.

17:01.458 --> 17:02.917
Yo!

17:03.000 --> 17:04.000
-OK.
-OK, Jo.

17:05.875 --> 17:09.583
Dora, hi, it's Dr. Grey calling.

17:09.667 --> 17:12.959
I-- I'm OK, thank you for asking.

17:13.041 --> 17:17.000
Dora, I-I'm so sorry
to tell you, but your father--

17:17.083 --> 17:19.583
his condition got much worse last night.

17:19.667 --> 17:22.667
So, um, I'm afraid if--

17:22.750 --> 17:25.125
if you do want to come
and say goodbye, then--

17:25.208 --> 17:27.583
then you should come soon.

17:28.417 --> 17:29.250
Now.

17:31.208 --> 17:32.542
OK.

17:32.625 --> 17:35.417
OK, uh, just call me when you're here,

17:35.500 --> 17:37.083
and I'll make the arrangements.

17:38.375 --> 17:40.875
OK. I'm-- I'm so-- I'm so sorry.

17:42.250 --> 17:43.125
OK.

17:46.458 --> 17:48.458
[sighs]

17:49.500 --> 17:52.291
[cellphone clicks, buttons clicking]

17:52.375 --> 17:54.291
[text chimes]

17:58.583 --> 18:00.291
[soft snore]

18:05.417 --> 18:06.917
[DeLuca] You're doing great, Cindy.

18:07.000 --> 18:08.458
Almost done, OK?

18:11.000 --> 18:12.250
I'm not Cindy.

18:17.417 --> 18:18.959
My name is Erin Banks.

18:19.875 --> 18:21.542
I'm from Scottsdale, Arizona.

18:25.083 --> 18:27.500
This photographer followed me on Snapchat.

18:28.959 --> 18:31.083
He said that he had a modeling agency

18:31.166 --> 18:32.625
and that I was beautiful.

18:33.375 --> 18:35.583
He wanted to meet, but my parents said no.

18:36.250 --> 18:37.875
<i>My sister said it was sketchy.</i>

18:40.834 --> 18:42.625
<i>But I snuck out to meet him.</i>

18:46.792 --> 18:48.000
<i>That was two years ago.</i>

18:48.083 --> 18:50.625
Two years? So she was fourteen.

18:50.709 --> 18:52.792
-Helm...
-[paper tears]

18:52.875 --> 18:56.000
Take this. Call the police immediately.

18:56.083 --> 18:57.750
Say to them what she just said.

18:57.834 --> 18:58.917
Her family needs to know

18:59.000 --> 19:01.000
their little girl is still alive. Go, go.

19:01.083 --> 19:03.083
[sighs]

19:04.458 --> 19:06.166
Lord, help us.

19:06.250 --> 19:08.083
[Erin] <i>My parents tried to warn me,</i>

19:08.166 --> 19:10.083
but I'm so dumb.

19:10.166 --> 19:11.333
I'm so stupid.

19:11.417 --> 19:13.375
Hey, hey, stop that. OK, listen to me.

19:13.458 --> 19:15.125
None of this is your fault, OK?

19:15.208 --> 19:16.083
None of it.

19:17.041 --> 19:19.834
It's Opal, and people like her.

19:19.917 --> 19:21.083
It's their fault.

19:22.166 --> 19:23.917
And we got you.

19:24.000 --> 19:26.583
And they're never going to
hurt you ever again, OK?

19:28.083 --> 19:30.750
Opal said that if I ran, she'd kill me,

19:30.834 --> 19:34.542
and if I told anyone, she'd find
my sister and take her, too.

19:43.542 --> 19:46.208
-[siren wails]
-[Koracick] Soak it in, kids.

19:46.291 --> 19:48.834
Bask in the glory of the PPE mother lode.

19:48.917 --> 19:50.583
It's beautiful.

19:50.667 --> 19:52.792
It came? It actually came!

19:52.875 --> 19:55.750
-[both laugh]
-I forgot what good news feels like.

19:55.834 --> 19:58.458
-Altman, can I help you?
-Uh, yeah.

19:58.542 --> 20:00.709
I mean, our nurses are using rubber bands

20:00.792 --> 20:01.667
to hold on their masks.

20:01.750 --> 20:02.834
Can't we help you open these?

20:02.917 --> 20:04.750
Or were you planning to sell them
on the black market?

20:04.834 --> 20:06.458
[laughs]

20:06.542 --> 20:07.709
Oh, my God, were you?

20:07.792 --> 20:10.375
No, no, I just--
We-- We need, uh, a system.

20:10.458 --> 20:12.291
Yeah, OK, well, you know, we open these,

20:12.375 --> 20:14.375
we take the masks,
and run around the hospital

20:14.458 --> 20:16.041
like Santa Claus on Christmas.
That's the system.

20:16.125 --> 20:18.000
Fine, fine, but you two stand guard

20:18.083 --> 20:19.625
in case someone sneaks in
from another hospital.

20:19.709 --> 20:22.041
-Are you serious?
-This stuff is paper gold, Tseng.

20:22.125 --> 20:23.709
So now you're
the best-educated security guard

20:23.792 --> 20:24.750
this side of the Mississippi.

20:24.834 --> 20:27.083
I got booties!

20:27.166 --> 20:28.333
Booties.

20:28.417 --> 20:30.125
Booties. Good. Booties are good.

20:30.208 --> 20:31.750
Yeah. OK, but we also need masks.

20:31.834 --> 20:34.208
Yeah, well, we also need... booties.

20:34.291 --> 20:36.667
You ordered masks, right?

20:36.750 --> 20:38.208
And gloves and shields?

20:38.291 --> 20:39.834
-[Koracick] Of course I did. I--
-[Taryn] These are all booties.

20:39.917 --> 20:41.458
-By the thousands.
-[Taryn] Booties, more booties.

20:41.542 --> 20:42.709
They're here, somewhere.

20:42.792 --> 20:43.750
<i>♪ I keep distance to everyone I see ♪</i>

20:43.834 --> 20:45.041
They're here some...

20:45.125 --> 20:46.208
<i>♪ Is it me or you? ♪</i>

20:46.291 --> 20:48.500
<i>♪ But something makin' me feel brand-new ♪</i>

20:57.542 --> 20:59.333
Damn it! Damn it!

20:59.417 --> 21:01.792
[Maggie] Oh, my God! Koracick!

21:01.875 --> 21:03.875
[grunting]

21:04.875 --> 21:05.750
[Teddy, echoing] Tom!

21:12.834 --> 21:15.208
[crying]

21:17.458 --> 21:19.625
[breathing heavily]

21:26.667 --> 21:28.417
[Jackson] He's still tachycardic.

21:28.500 --> 21:31.125
His body's so stressed from the burns.

21:31.208 --> 21:33.500
God, it's so hot in here.

21:33.583 --> 21:36.542
It has to be. I mean, the burns mean
his body can't regulate temperature,

21:36.625 --> 21:39.542
-so we got to crank the whole room way up.
-I know that.

21:40.542 --> 21:42.375
I wasn't saying you didn't, Jo.

21:42.458 --> 21:44.041
OK, then why even say it?

21:44.125 --> 21:45.959
You said it was hot. I said why.

21:46.041 --> 21:47.458
OK? I thought
we were just stating facts.

21:47.542 --> 21:49.625
[doorbell rings]

21:49.709 --> 21:52.250
Hey. I, uh, I drank some in the elevator

21:52.333 --> 21:54.166
to, like, make it less weird.

21:54.250 --> 21:56.917
Oh! Wine!

21:57.000 --> 21:58.667
[Jackson] Yeah, which is now embarrassing

21:58.792 --> 21:59.792
because I realize

21:59.875 --> 22:01.542
that I kind of set this up as a date,

22:01.625 --> 22:03.250
and it's definitely not a date.

22:03.333 --> 22:04.834
I mean, I didn't bother wearing pants,

22:04.917 --> 22:07.166
but it's really sweet.

22:07.250 --> 22:10.375
Whoa! [laughing] Oh, my God,
is that your date food?

22:10.458 --> 22:13.458
-That is not--
-Oh, my God, Jackson.

22:13.542 --> 22:15.750
No girl wants to take their clothes off

22:15.834 --> 22:17.667
after eating cheese and cured meat.

22:17.792 --> 22:20.250
Thanks for coming over
and openly mocking me.

22:20.333 --> 22:22.709
This is-- It's totally
acceptable date food.

22:22.792 --> 22:24.458
-Wait.
-[romantic music playing]

22:24.542 --> 22:26.000
Is that Kenny G?

22:26.083 --> 22:27.583
[gasps]

22:27.667 --> 22:30.667
Do you only have romantic soft pillow sex?

22:30.750 --> 22:32.917
That's not-- It's on, like, a shuffle.

22:33.000 --> 22:35.667
Mm. Mm.

22:35.750 --> 22:37.333
I hate you. Gimme that.

22:39.208 --> 22:40.667
[Jo gasps] Wow.

22:41.458 --> 22:42.333
What now?

22:42.417 --> 22:45.125
No, I just realized I've never
dated a rich guy before.

22:45.208 --> 22:46.667
I mean, doctors have money,

22:46.750 --> 22:49.000
but you're, like, collect-art rich.

22:49.083 --> 22:51.250
Wow, that would weird me out.

22:51.333 --> 22:53.792
Well, it's a good thing that
we're not dating then, isn't it?

22:55.417 --> 22:56.291
Right.

22:57.583 --> 22:58.750
You're just a bridge.

22:59.542 --> 23:00.709
I'm just a bridge.

23:07.917 --> 23:09.875
Are you sure this is what you want?

23:09.959 --> 23:11.041
Mm-hmm.

23:19.417 --> 23:21.417
[crying]

23:22.625 --> 23:25.083
Are you-- Oh, oh, OK.

23:25.166 --> 23:26.166
We c-- We should stop.

23:26.250 --> 23:27.458
No, no, no, I'm OK. Let's keep going.

23:27.542 --> 23:29.500
-I don't think-- Jo--
-I'm OK. I'm OK.

23:29.583 --> 23:31.250
-It's OK. We should--
-[crying] No, no, I really--

23:31.333 --> 23:33.542
I really want to have sex with you.

23:33.625 --> 23:35.917
I really do. Please, let's keep going.

23:36.000 --> 23:37.125
OK, listen, it's OK.

23:37.208 --> 23:38.875
I think we can-- we can try another time.

23:38.959 --> 23:40.709
I'm sorry.

23:40.792 --> 23:42.166
-Sit down.
-I'm sorry.

23:42.250 --> 23:43.834
I'll get you some water.

23:43.917 --> 23:45.458
[crying]

23:49.834 --> 23:50.959
I'm so sorry.

23:51.041 --> 23:52.375
No, you have nothing to be sorry about.

23:52.458 --> 23:54.375
Don't worry about it.

23:54.458 --> 23:55.792
[crying]

23:58.166 --> 23:59.625
They said they wanted to talk to my boss.

23:59.709 --> 24:01.000
Then tell them <i>you're </i>the boss next time.

24:01.083 --> 24:03.583
-Really?
-Hello. I'm Dr. Miranda Bailey.

24:03.625 --> 24:05.542
[Steve] Uh, uh, Kayden Lee is our son.
He was in a fire.

24:05.625 --> 24:07.542
Kayden is only 18.
We should be allowed to be in there.

24:07.625 --> 24:09.834
I know this is a scary situation.

24:09.917 --> 24:13.375
I'm a parent. Believe me,
I understand your frustration.

24:13.458 --> 24:16.750
But you have my word as chief
that all of your children

24:16.834 --> 24:19.291
are receiving the best possible care.

24:19.375 --> 24:21.333
But we just need you to bear
with us a little while longer.

24:21.417 --> 24:23.583
Excuse me. Uh, Aaron Morris.
Any word on Frankie?

24:23.667 --> 24:26.250
-Uh, which one is Frankie?
-He's immunocompromised.

24:26.333 --> 24:27.208
He got a kidney donation

24:27.291 --> 24:29.291
for polycystic kidney disease
just two months ago.

24:29.417 --> 24:30.458
He's high risk for Covid.

24:30.542 --> 24:32.834
-Then why was he at a party?
-Schmitt.

24:32.917 --> 24:34.667
-Frankie Morris.
-Yes.

24:34.750 --> 24:36.542
Uh, he must still be en route.

24:36.625 --> 24:37.917
I'll look into it myself.

24:38.917 --> 24:41.208
Tell Kayden he's not alone.
Mom and Dad are here.

24:41.291 --> 24:43.667
I cannot do this, Steve.
I need to be with him.

24:43.750 --> 24:46.041
He's our baby. [crying]

24:49.458 --> 24:51.208
[Bailey] We still haven't heard
anything from her family?

24:51.291 --> 24:52.875
[Taryn] Her family still live in Arizona,

24:52.959 --> 24:55.083
sister goes to school in Portland.

24:55.166 --> 24:57.291
I'm not sure if missing persons
was able to reach them.

24:57.375 --> 24:58.667
Well, find out. I don't want her

24:58.750 --> 25:01.208
waking up alone in an empty ICU!

25:01.291 --> 25:02.125
Go on!

25:04.375 --> 25:06.417
Bailey, if this is too much for you,
I can take over.

25:06.542 --> 25:08.792
I betrayed her once.
I'm not doing that again.

25:08.875 --> 25:11.333
I looked her in the eye

25:11.417 --> 25:14.125
and told DeLuca to send her home.

25:14.208 --> 25:15.250
With a monster.

25:15.333 --> 25:17.875
Well, you assessed the situation
as best you could.

25:17.959 --> 25:19.417
And you were distracted
because DeLuca was--

25:19.500 --> 25:21.834
DeLuca-- I don't know what
we're gonna do with DeLuca.

25:21.917 --> 25:25.750
-[sighs]
-I mean, I-I know what he's feeling.

25:25.834 --> 25:27.750
At least in part.

25:27.834 --> 25:30.542
I know what it feels like to want help

25:30.625 --> 25:32.375
but be afraid of it at the same time.

25:32.458 --> 25:35.417
Richard Webber all but put
the pills in my mouth.

25:35.500 --> 25:38.583
I had given up, but he never did.

25:38.667 --> 25:40.709
Well, maybe that's what we need to do.

25:40.792 --> 25:41.834
Just not give up.

25:41.917 --> 25:43.000
Tissue grasper.

25:45.834 --> 25:46.959
-Frankie...
-Morris.

25:47.041 --> 25:48.166
His father was notified

25:48.250 --> 25:49.500
he was being brought here from the fire.

25:49.583 --> 25:51.166
Frankie Morris. He's not here yet.

25:51.250 --> 25:52.834
[sighs] What did they do?

25:52.917 --> 25:54.333
Stop for frozen yogurt on the way?

25:54.417 --> 25:56.625
We're not even supposed
to be open to trauma.

25:56.709 --> 25:58.625
You think he was turned away?

25:58.709 --> 26:00.000
I'll try to find out.

26:00.083 --> 26:01.542
Uh, uh, Bailey.

26:01.625 --> 26:03.333
Uh, ah.

26:03.417 --> 26:04.709
Um, I was thinking.

26:04.792 --> 26:08.625
I saw some nurses wiping down
their masks with bleach.

26:08.709 --> 26:09.792
Now, I know that can't be good,

26:09.875 --> 26:10.959
so what I was wondering was can I--

26:11.041 --> 26:13.709
You went through the whole stack
of safety precautions?

26:13.834 --> 26:14.959
I-I-I-- What was I say--

26:15.041 --> 26:17.083
You committed all
of those protocols to memory?

26:19.083 --> 26:21.625
Look, this is no longer
the hospital that you left.

26:21.709 --> 26:23.834
And if you're going to insist
on being here,

26:23.917 --> 26:26.583
then you are going to need
to know how we operate now.

26:26.709 --> 26:30.000
So when I tell you
to read the safety protocol,

26:30.083 --> 26:32.583
I mean read the damn safety protocol!

26:42.166 --> 26:44.125
[woman, over PA]
<i>Dr. Madigan </i><i>to the Covid floor.</i>

26:44.208 --> 26:46.375
<i>Dr. Madigan </i><i>to the Covid floor.</i>

26:48.125 --> 26:50.417
[cellphone rings]

26:52.417 --> 26:53.375
[sighs]

26:55.333 --> 26:56.291
-[cellphone clicks]
-Hey.

26:56.375 --> 26:57.834
Yeah, so when I said goodbye earlier,

26:57.917 --> 26:59.583
something kinda slipped out.

26:59.667 --> 27:02.917
Hmm. You're gonna need
to be more specific.

27:03.000 --> 27:06.667
Oh, you mean when you dropped
a "love you" on me

27:06.750 --> 27:07.875
and then jumped off our call?

27:07.959 --> 27:10.542
<i>-Right, OK, </i><i>so you heard.</i>
-[chuckles]

27:10.667 --> 27:12.917
Yeah, so, um, s-so, yeah,

27:13.000 --> 27:14.125
I wasn't really saying that to you.

27:14.208 --> 27:16.000
That was to my colleague Kingsley.

27:16.083 --> 27:18.750
<i>It's this little initiative</i>
<i>we started at my hospital.</i>

27:18.834 --> 27:20.250
<i>It's kind of like </i><i>a morale boost,</i>

27:20.333 --> 27:21.792
so that the whole staff feels valued.

27:21.875 --> 27:24.083
Oh, yeah, that makes way more sense

27:24.166 --> 27:26.709
than you saying it to me
because that would be--

27:26.792 --> 27:28.375
Ridiculous, yeah, I know.

27:29.291 --> 27:31.667
And maybe scare you away.

27:31.750 --> 27:32.834
For real, though. Did I freak you out?

27:33.583 --> 27:35.667
Weirdly only a little.

27:35.750 --> 27:37.875
<i>OK, good.</i>

27:37.959 --> 27:40.125
Because if I lost
the one place in the world

27:40.208 --> 27:42.875
where I actually manage
to feel good during this mess,

27:42.959 --> 27:45.333
-I think I'd be done for.
-Me, too.

27:47.542 --> 27:49.583
And somehow you just made it more romantic

27:49.667 --> 27:50.667
than saying "love."

27:50.792 --> 27:52.917
-See how I do?
<i>-Hm.</i>

27:53.000 --> 27:55.875
-Talk later?
-If we're still alive.

27:57.208 --> 27:58.625
[cellphone beeps]

28:00.250 --> 28:02.250
[chuckles]

28:20.875 --> 28:22.291
[Richard] Excuse me.

28:22.375 --> 28:25.083
We have more signs in this place
than Times Square,

28:25.166 --> 28:26.250
and they're very clear.

28:26.333 --> 28:28.458
The few visitors we have right now

28:28.542 --> 28:30.458
have to be accompanied
by a hospital employee.

28:30.542 --> 28:32.417
So either you have been misplaced

28:32.500 --> 28:33.917
or you're not supposed to be here.

28:34.041 --> 28:36.083
My son is in here. Kayden Lee.

28:36.166 --> 28:37.917
I know it's against the rules
for me to be here,

28:38.000 --> 28:39.041
but he was burned.

28:39.125 --> 28:41.542
He was burned so badly
that he needs surgery.

28:41.625 --> 28:44.625
He just turned 18, and I-- and I--

28:44.709 --> 28:46.208
and I know that means that he's an adult,

28:46.291 --> 28:49.375
that he drives a car
and he's dating someone,

28:49.458 --> 28:50.875
and he does his own laundry

28:50.959 --> 28:52.834
because we wanted to make sure
of that before college.

28:52.917 --> 28:55.750
But he still has the same smile

28:55.834 --> 28:57.959
that he had when he was a baby,

28:58.041 --> 29:01.333
and he still says "I love you"
before leaving the house,

29:01.417 --> 29:02.375
and he won't shut the door

29:02.458 --> 29:04.667
unless I say "I love you" back.

29:05.458 --> 29:06.542
So he needs me.

29:06.625 --> 29:09.250
He needs to hear my voice

29:09.333 --> 29:11.250
and he'll know that I love him

29:11.333 --> 29:14.750
and that everything is going to be OK.

29:17.041 --> 29:21.166
I know what it's like
to worry about someone

29:21.250 --> 29:23.041
so much you think it'll break you.

29:29.000 --> 29:31.166
-Come with me.
-Oh, thank you.

29:31.250 --> 29:32.250
Thank you.

29:43.166 --> 29:44.458
What is this?

29:44.542 --> 29:47.834
Andrew, the people in this room
love you, respect you,

29:47.917 --> 29:50.834
and care about you,
and they want you to know that.

29:50.917 --> 29:52.417
[scoffs] This is--

29:52.500 --> 29:55.208
No, no, humor us, please, please.

29:59.500 --> 30:01.500
[Carina]
A-A-Andrea, the day you were born,

30:01.583 --> 30:02.959
Nonna was babysitting me.

30:03.041 --> 30:05.834
And-- And, uh, when she told me
I had a baby brother,

30:05.917 --> 30:07.917
I-I-I ran outside and I splashed around

30:08.000 --> 30:09.625
in the puddles of rain and--

30:09.709 --> 30:11.792
and shouted at the sky
because I was so happy.

30:11.875 --> 30:13.041
I, um...

30:15.500 --> 30:18.917
You-- You will always be my baby brother.

30:18.959 --> 30:20.458
And I know you're hurting right now.

30:20.542 --> 30:21.959
I know that.

30:22.041 --> 30:23.667
But you don't have to be.

30:23.750 --> 30:24.917
There is help for you.

30:25.000 --> 30:27.250
All of us want to help you.

30:29.083 --> 30:33.709
DeLuca, even if you hadn't
saved my life, I'd be here.

30:33.792 --> 30:36.333
I've seen class after class
come through this program.

30:36.417 --> 30:40.917
I've done it enough to know when
someone has something special.

30:42.333 --> 30:43.500
Don't throw this away.

30:43.583 --> 30:45.166
[Meredith] What seems like a weakness

30:45.250 --> 30:47.959
is actually a strength-- if you get help.

30:49.291 --> 30:52.959
Because you care so deeply.

30:54.041 --> 30:56.917
You fight so hard for your patients,

30:57.000 --> 30:58.333
for the people you love.

30:59.417 --> 31:01.208
That's not illness. That's you.

31:02.375 --> 31:05.959
You-- You know I live
with obsessive compulsive disorder.

31:06.959 --> 31:08.166
But I take medication.

31:08.250 --> 31:11.458
I get therapy, and I stay on top of it.

31:11.542 --> 31:14.667
And, no, it is not always easy for me.

31:16.083 --> 31:17.375
Look, you're not alone.

31:18.333 --> 31:21.458
You have an illness,
but there's no shame in that.

31:22.542 --> 31:23.667
-No shame?
-No.

31:23.750 --> 31:24.709
That's a joke, right?

31:24.792 --> 31:26.542
[therapist] Why do you think it's a joke?

31:26.625 --> 31:27.750
To say there's no shame?

31:28.792 --> 31:30.917
My whole life, I've had one goal.

31:32.041 --> 31:34.542
One thing that would mean I did OK.

31:35.834 --> 31:37.208
Don't end up like my dad.

31:40.125 --> 31:44.291
I wanted it more than being a surgeon.

31:45.625 --> 31:46.625
One thing.

31:47.417 --> 31:48.417
And I just...

31:49.667 --> 31:50.542
I failed.

31:50.625 --> 31:52.458
No, you're not like him.

31:52.542 --> 31:53.834
I don't care what you think, OK?

31:53.917 --> 31:55.667
I don't care about Bailey's OCD.

31:55.750 --> 31:57.125
I don't care about saving Richard's life.

31:57.208 --> 31:59.458
I would give up every life
I have ever saved

31:59.542 --> 32:01.208
if I could just not feel like this.

32:02.458 --> 32:03.542
I'd give up knowing you!

32:03.625 --> 32:06.542
[crying] God!

32:08.959 --> 32:11.959
[crying]

32:14.792 --> 32:15.625
[Carina] Hey.

32:18.625 --> 32:19.667
Hey.

32:20.709 --> 32:22.500
[DeLuca] I know I'm not OK.

32:25.500 --> 32:27.667
I just don't know what to do.

32:27.750 --> 32:32.000
OK. You listen to the people
that know what to do

32:32.083 --> 32:33.917
and let them help you, Andrea.

32:34.000 --> 32:35.333
Th-That's it.

32:35.417 --> 32:38.166
<i>♪ It's there in your eyes ♪</i>

32:41.125 --> 32:43.500
<i>♪ The way this world ♪</i>

32:43.625 --> 32:45.083
<i>♪ Has held us down ♪</i>

32:45.166 --> 32:46.542
All we're asking you to do

32:46.625 --> 32:50.583
is fight as hard for yourself
as you do for everybody else.

32:52.625 --> 32:54.041
<i>♪ We're on our own ♪</i>

32:55.250 --> 32:56.875
<i>♪ At least for now ♪</i>

32:56.959 --> 32:58.041
<i>♪ Just ♪</i>

32:58.125 --> 33:01.041
<i>♪ Surviving, surviving ♪</i>

33:01.125 --> 33:02.083
<i>♪ And nothing else ♪</i>

33:02.166 --> 33:04.083
-OK.
-OK.

33:05.917 --> 33:06.917
OK.

33:09.834 --> 33:10.667
Perez.

33:11.500 --> 33:12.375
It's Grey.

33:12.458 --> 33:14.125
Get someone to cover your shift

33:14.208 --> 33:16.500
so you can walk Dora up
so she can say goodbye.

33:17.917 --> 33:18.917
Yep, that's it.

33:19.000 --> 33:20.542
Walk her up so she can say goodbye.

33:20.625 --> 33:21.583
Thank you. [cellphone clicks]

33:21.667 --> 33:23.041
<i>♪ The room in a spin ♪</i>

33:23.166 --> 33:26.834
<i>♪ I hear the howling of the wind ♪</i>

33:26.917 --> 33:29.250
<i>♪ And the pounding of the rain ♪</i>

33:29.333 --> 33:33.208
<i>♪ And I'd give everything to dream again ♪</i>

33:33.291 --> 33:35.417
<i>♪ There must be more than ♪</i>

33:35.500 --> 33:38.250
<i>♪ Surviving, surviving ♪</i>

33:38.333 --> 33:41.083
<i>♪ Surviving, surviving ♪</i>

33:41.166 --> 33:42.792
<i>♪ And nothing else ♪</i>

33:42.875 --> 33:43.750
[crying]

33:43.834 --> 33:46.834
<i>♪ Surviving, surviving ♪</i>

33:46.917 --> 33:49.458
<i>♪ Surviving, surviving ♪</i>

33:49.542 --> 33:52.500
<i>♪ Surviving, surviving ♪</i>

33:52.667 --> 33:56.583
<i>♪ And nothing else ♪</i>

33:56.667 --> 33:58.208
I'll clean all this up.

34:00.792 --> 34:04.667
<i>♪ I'd give everything to dream again ♪</i>

34:04.750 --> 34:05.834
<i>♪ Ohhh ♪</i>

34:05.917 --> 34:08.041
I'll clean... that up.

34:09.625 --> 34:10.750
[sighs]

34:11.709 --> 34:12.709
Hey.

34:23.291 --> 34:24.625
Where have you been?

34:24.709 --> 34:26.875
I-I was at home.

34:26.959 --> 34:30.792
If you're not here
and you don't answer your phone,

34:30.875 --> 34:32.709
then no one knows where you are

34:32.792 --> 34:36.083
and nobody knows that you're OK.

34:36.792 --> 34:37.917
I turned the ringer off

34:38.000 --> 34:39.667
and I crashed the second I got home, OK?

34:39.750 --> 34:41.583
The therapist says that if I don't sleep,

34:41.667 --> 34:43.792
the mania can creep back in.

34:46.083 --> 34:47.208
Who died?

34:47.333 --> 34:48.667
Everyone.

34:49.542 --> 34:50.750
Marvin Lindstrom,

34:50.834 --> 34:52.458
Doris Sanchez,

34:52.542 --> 34:53.583
Tom Richardson.

34:53.667 --> 34:54.583
You treated him.

34:54.667 --> 34:56.542
Yeah, the retired choir director.

34:56.625 --> 34:58.959
He-- He loved fishing.

34:59.041 --> 35:00.500
[sighs]

35:01.000 --> 35:03.375
And I'm sorry I wasn't here, Mer.

35:06.417 --> 35:07.417
You're OK?

35:08.208 --> 35:11.542
Yeah, I'm-- I'm OK.

35:11.625 --> 35:12.959
I'm glad you're OK.

35:13.834 --> 35:15.375
Make sure people know where you are.

35:15.458 --> 35:17.792
[Joanna Jones' "Freedom" plays]

35:17.875 --> 35:19.667
[elevator bell dings]

35:19.750 --> 35:22.750
So, Dr. Grey and I were able
to repair Erin's hernia,

35:22.834 --> 35:26.083
but there was a great deal
of inflammation in her abdomen.

35:26.166 --> 35:29.667
So we are giving her
a course of IV antibiotics.

35:29.792 --> 35:30.959
You're going to have to say all this again

35:31.041 --> 35:32.583
for my parents when they get here.

35:33.500 --> 35:35.333
I still can't believe any of this.

35:35.417 --> 35:36.917
We-- We looked for her forever.

35:37.000 --> 35:38.750
[sniffles] We looked for her everywhere.

35:38.834 --> 35:40.041
<i>♪ Those winds of change ♪</i>

35:40.125 --> 35:43.000
Well, we can't stress enough
how much she's been through.

35:43.083 --> 35:45.875
She's going to need years
of support and therapy.

35:45.959 --> 35:47.166
Of course, whatever she needs.

35:47.250 --> 35:49.458
I'm not sure I'm gonna let her
out of my sight ag--

35:49.542 --> 35:50.375
[gasps]

35:50.458 --> 35:52.291
<i>♪ It feels like freedom ♪</i>

35:52.417 --> 35:53.250
Abby?

35:54.750 --> 35:56.041
I'm here, Erin.

35:56.125 --> 35:57.291
I'm here. Oh, my God.

35:57.375 --> 35:59.542
<i>♪ Storm clouds are breakin' ♪</i>

35:59.625 --> 36:02.333
<i>♪ Storm clouds are breakin'</i>
<i>Oh, yeah ♪</i>

36:02.417 --> 36:03.709
-[both crying]
-I'm so sorry.

36:03.792 --> 36:05.041
<i>♪ My worries, they are fadin' ♪</i>

36:05.125 --> 36:06.500
-I'm so sorry.
-It's not your fault.

36:06.583 --> 36:08.375
It's not your fault.

36:08.458 --> 36:09.750
It's not your fault.

36:09.834 --> 36:10.667
<i>♪ And, oh ♪</i>

36:10.750 --> 36:12.166
<i>♪ Oh, freedom ♪</i>

36:12.250 --> 36:13.792
<i>♪ Oh, yeah ♪</i>

36:13.875 --> 36:15.500
<i>♪ Freedom ♪</i>

36:15.583 --> 36:18.250
<i>♪ It feels like freedom ♪</i>

36:18.333 --> 36:19.959
<i>♪ Oh, freedom ♪</i>

36:21.875 --> 36:24.875
<i>♪ And my sisters and brothers ♪</i>

36:25.000 --> 36:26.125
<i>♪ Sisters and brothers ♪</i>

36:26.208 --> 36:27.041
Kayden.

36:27.125 --> 36:28.166
<i>♪ Oh, yeah ♪</i>

36:28.250 --> 36:29.125
[cries]

36:29.208 --> 36:32.291
<i>♪ I see 'em comin' together, ooh ♪</i>

36:32.375 --> 36:34.875
<i>♪ Comin' together, ooh ♪</i>

36:35.166 --> 36:36.458
<i>♪ And, oh ♪</i>

36:36.542 --> 36:40.834
<i>♪ I'm ready now to move on ♪</i>

36:40.917 --> 36:42.834
What the hell are you doing?
You know that's not allowed.

36:42.917 --> 36:44.458
If Bailey asks, I'll tell her

36:44.542 --> 36:46.375
that I didn't get to
that part of the manual.

36:46.458 --> 36:47.750
<i>♪ The sun is comin' up again ♪</i>

36:47.834 --> 36:49.500
Can you give her a couple minutes?

36:49.583 --> 36:50.417
[sighs]

36:50.500 --> 36:51.625
[Deborah] Mama's here.

36:52.458 --> 36:53.625
Can you hear me?

36:55.041 --> 36:58.125
I'm here, and I love you.

36:58.208 --> 37:00.625
I love you, too.

37:00.709 --> 37:02.750
<i>♪ I know ♪</i>

37:02.834 --> 37:07.041
<i>♪ It feels like freedom ♪</i>

37:09.208 --> 37:10.041
Richard.

37:10.125 --> 37:11.750
O-O-OK, I know it's just a start, but--

37:11.834 --> 37:13.375
If you haven't gotten through
the new protocols,

37:13.458 --> 37:14.542
then I'm not interested.

37:14.625 --> 37:17.875
You are not my mother,
and you are not my teacher.

37:17.959 --> 37:19.959
You are my colleague
and you are my friend--

37:20.041 --> 37:21.041
And I am your boss.

37:21.125 --> 37:23.625
I am your boss and it is my job to--

37:23.709 --> 37:25.375
Well, don't tell me what your job is.

37:25.458 --> 37:26.834
I taught you your job.

37:26.917 --> 37:28.834
I taught you your whole damn job.

37:28.917 --> 37:30.750
And now suddenly you don't
want to let me do mine?

37:30.834 --> 37:33.333
I brought you down here
for some good news,

37:33.458 --> 37:34.375
but you're convinced that I'm--

37:34.458 --> 37:36.834
I'm incompetent and infirm,
and you won't even hear it.

37:36.959 --> 37:38.875
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa. What good news?

37:41.125 --> 37:44.083
Your staff is reusing PPE,

37:44.166 --> 37:45.875
and cleaning them with bacterial wipes...

37:45.959 --> 37:48.542
-Yeah.
-...which deteriorates the mask.

37:51.625 --> 37:53.709
[sighs] Now they don't have to.

37:54.458 --> 37:55.500
You're welcome.

37:56.125 --> 37:58.667
[Bailey] Oh, my God.

37:58.750 --> 37:59.750
[sighs]

38:00.750 --> 38:01.834
It's genius.

38:01.917 --> 38:03.250
[laughs]

38:03.333 --> 38:05.166
-You're genius.
-I know.

38:05.250 --> 38:06.750
I'm not sure how you forgot.

38:06.834 --> 38:08.959
[scoffs] I did not.

38:10.125 --> 38:12.250
And it's not about your ability, Richard.

38:12.333 --> 38:13.875
It's about your vulnerability.

38:13.959 --> 38:16.542
You know you are high risk
for Covid right now.

38:16.625 --> 38:19.000
Look, you have already given
more of yourself

38:19.083 --> 38:21.375
to this hospital than anyone ever could.

38:21.458 --> 38:24.083
And you have overcome, you have suffered,

38:24.166 --> 38:27.709
and you are why this hospital
is as good as it is today.

38:27.792 --> 38:30.208
Y-You're why I am as good as I am today.

38:30.291 --> 38:34.750
And you, Richard, have earned
the right to stay home,

38:34.834 --> 38:38.000
to stay safe, and to rest.

38:38.083 --> 38:39.625
This thing, it's...

38:39.709 --> 38:42.667
[sighs] It's-- It's--
It's only going to get worse.

38:45.208 --> 38:47.917
Every relationship
I've ever had has failed.

38:49.125 --> 38:50.417
Except this one.

38:51.250 --> 38:53.917
And this place.

38:55.291 --> 38:56.917
I will find no peace--

38:57.000 --> 38:58.750
no peace--

39:00.375 --> 39:01.834
if I have to leave it.

39:01.917 --> 39:03.458
[voice breaking] You...

39:04.625 --> 39:06.542
are going to give me
a second heart attack,

39:06.625 --> 39:07.625
you know that?

39:07.709 --> 39:09.625
-Bailey...
-[sighs]

39:09.709 --> 39:11.208
...you know I got to tell you

39:11.291 --> 39:14.750
that this place couldn't ask
for a better chief.

39:14.834 --> 39:15.792
I'm in awe.

39:17.375 --> 39:18.959
Even though I taught you most of it.

39:19.041 --> 39:19.875
[Bailey] You know...

39:29.000 --> 39:30.500
[monitor beeping]

39:35.959 --> 39:37.000
[Jo] Hey.

39:38.250 --> 39:39.166
Hey.

39:39.291 --> 39:40.834
How's he doing?

39:40.917 --> 39:42.458
-Well, he's stable.
-OK.

39:42.542 --> 39:44.667
I think his visit from his mom helped.

39:44.750 --> 39:45.583
Right.

39:48.375 --> 39:50.667
I'd like to apologize to you
if that'll help.

39:50.750 --> 39:52.834
I mean, I'm not exactly sure what I did

39:52.917 --> 39:56.208
-to make you so angry, but--
-Angry? I'm-- No, I'm not angry.

39:56.291 --> 39:58.750
I-- I was just hot.

40:02.792 --> 40:04.500
Jackson. [sighs]

40:04.583 --> 40:06.125
I am mortified.

40:07.375 --> 40:09.750
All the time, every minute
that I'm around you.

40:09.834 --> 40:14.250
I... cried into your mouth.

40:14.333 --> 40:18.542
I mean, I'm-- I'm pretty sure
that I snotted in your mouth.

40:18.625 --> 40:20.667
And I-I-- You were trying
to do me a favor

40:20.750 --> 40:23.667
-and I just-- I--
-It was a favor you weren't ready for.

40:24.625 --> 40:27.166
-I really wasn't.
-It's fine. You--

40:27.250 --> 40:28.959
Look, you've been through hell, OK?

40:29.041 --> 40:30.125
You were doing your best.

40:30.208 --> 40:31.417
You're still doing your best.

40:31.500 --> 40:34.709
And we are, um, friends.

40:35.750 --> 40:39.667
So if you can get over the mortification

40:39.750 --> 40:42.625
and stop treating me like crap,
I figure we're all good.

40:42.709 --> 40:44.667
Can we just pretend it never happened?

40:45.625 --> 40:46.458
Done.

40:46.542 --> 40:49.000
OK. Alright.

40:54.917 --> 40:56.250
[Deborah] I saw Kayden.

40:56.333 --> 40:57.792
It's bad.

40:58.917 --> 41:01.041
[voice breaking] He was so bandaged

41:01.125 --> 41:03.125
that I couldn't see his face.

41:03.250 --> 41:06.291
-One second, OK. Hi, um, Mr. Morris.
-Yes?

41:06.375 --> 41:09.375
Hey, your son Frankie was taken
to Seattle Presbyterian

41:09.458 --> 41:11.166
-because we're a Covid center--
-Oh, my God.

41:11.250 --> 41:14.041
No, they are understaffed,

41:14.125 --> 41:15.542
so they turned away his ambulance.

41:15.625 --> 41:17.291
-Are you kidding me?
-I've been in touch with my husband,

41:17.375 --> 41:18.500
who is a first responder.

41:18.583 --> 41:20.125
They're bringing him back here.

41:20.208 --> 41:22.834
He is stable, right?
He should be here momentarily.

41:22.917 --> 41:24.250
Oh, my God.

41:24.333 --> 41:26.583
-OK. Thank you.
-OK?

41:26.667 --> 41:29.041
-Oh, God.
-[sighs] OK.

41:31.875 --> 41:33.250
Hey, Mr. Bronson said his wife was here,

41:33.333 --> 41:34.333
but I can't find her.

41:34.417 --> 41:37.041
Can you just let her know
that his ORIF went fine?

41:39.583 --> 41:40.959
I hope you're doing OK.

41:42.834 --> 41:44.333
Because I'm not.

41:45.000 --> 41:46.792
I hit 100 this morning.

41:46.917 --> 41:48.917
One hundred times I've had to tell someone

41:49.000 --> 41:50.667
that their loved one has died.

41:50.750 --> 41:52.709
That's 10 times as much as I've had to do

41:52.792 --> 41:53.875
since I started here.

41:53.959 --> 41:55.917
And it's making me wonder how much longer

41:56.000 --> 42:01.709
I can keep doing this
because 100 is a... big number.

42:01.792 --> 42:05.792
And I'm afraid of getting to
a place where it's not so big.

42:05.875 --> 42:07.583
And I know that we're not together,

42:07.667 --> 42:11.333
but you're still a person
that I care about and...

42:11.417 --> 42:12.458
I don't know.

42:12.542 --> 42:15.542
I-I-I thought that you might
want to know how I'm doing.

42:15.625 --> 42:17.458
Which is terrible.

42:18.917 --> 42:20.959
And I really hope that you're OK.

42:25.959 --> 42:26.959
I'm fine.

42:28.417 --> 42:30.375
[Aaron] No, Conor said
Kayden started the fire.

42:30.458 --> 42:32.250
Oh, so it's-- it's his fault?

42:33.250 --> 42:34.625
They shouldn't have even been out there,

42:34.709 --> 42:36.041
but they felt sorry for Frankie.

42:36.125 --> 42:38.000
Wait a minute.
You think that this is Frankie's fault?

42:38.083 --> 42:39.500
Posting all the time about how sad he is

42:39.583 --> 42:40.625
he can't be with his friends.

42:40.709 --> 42:42.834
He missed a year of school
when he was sick.

42:42.917 --> 42:44.709
Of course he wanted to see his friends.

42:44.792 --> 42:47.208
And, hey, I don't need a lecture
from Mr. Lakehouse here, OK?

42:47.291 --> 42:48.667
[Bailey] OK, everyone, let's just settle.

42:48.709 --> 42:50.458
We all follow each other on Instagram.

42:50.542 --> 42:52.792
Did you really think we weren't
gonna see you grilling

42:52.875 --> 42:55.250
every night with half the neighborhood?

42:55.333 --> 42:56.834
And no one in masks!

42:56.917 --> 42:58.333
You know, kids learn by example.

42:58.417 --> 43:00.041
Well, Kayden's example is a selfish moron.

43:00.125 --> 43:02.583
-[people gasp]
-[Bailey] Stop, both of you!

43:02.667 --> 43:04.709
-Steve, stop! Cut it out right now!
-Schmitt, call security!

43:04.792 --> 43:08.333
[Meredith] <i>Disaster has a tendency to melt</i>
<i>away everything else in life.</i>

43:08.417 --> 43:10.750
Selfish son of a bitch!

43:12.041 --> 43:12.875
[Deborah] Steve!

43:12.959 --> 43:15.583
[Meredith] <i>So if you want to know</i>
<i>who you'll be in a disaster,</i>

43:15.667 --> 43:18.458
<i>-ask yourself...</i>
-Security!

43:19.542 --> 43:20.583
<i>...who am I now?</i>
